description: The Atlanta Showroom is offering this 1967 Ford Mustang.  The inline six on this pony car is owner stated original and the original bill of sale from Mitchell Howell Ford in Virginia is available to the next owner.  This Mustang came with a black vinyl roof, cruise-o-matic S/S, 695X14 tires AM radio, wire wheel covers, and front and rear floor mats for an additional option cost of $446.77.  This pony has AC now to keep you cool in the hot summer months when you are enjoying your stang around town or going to the show.  The 1967 Ford Mustang was the first time since its beginning to be significantly changed. It was similar to its original style but just bigger. The grille features a larger opening and the feature lines on the side led to larger simulated air scoops. The taillight were three vertical lenses on each side of a concave panel and the gas cap was located in the center of the panel. About seven percent of the 1967 mustangs had the four-speed manual transmission, 98 percent had bucket seats, 15 percent had vinyl tops, 16 percent had air conditioning, and a rare feature was the dual exhaust found on about 25,000 cars. Options include: AC, wire wheels, radial tires. This To view the car in greater detail, including 100+ HD photos and HD video, please visit www.gatewayclassiccars.com. For more information please call the Atlanta showroom at 678-894-4833.
